<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=6473&amp;p=62584#p62584"><![CDATA[
Lots of games have push button codes. They've lost popularity in recent years though. But for a time they were hidden in many games. <br /><br />Interesting thing about Contra is that Contra 3 on SNES had the 30 lives code removed from the US version. The japanese version has it making it much easier for them if they knew the code. No clue if the European version had the code or not.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=1726">MottZilla</a> — Mon Jun 07, 2010 1:43 pm</p><hr />
